Environment Variables

You’ll need to securely configure these in a .env file or secrets manager:

env

SHODAN_API_KEY=your_key_here
VIRUSTOTAL_API_KEY=your_key_here
GOOGLE_SAFE_BROWSING_KEY=your_key_here
DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@host:port/db
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
Installation Notes
OWASP ZAP: Run via Docker for simplicity:

bash

docker pull owasp/zap2docker-stable
docker run -t owasp/zap2docker-stable zap-baseline.py -t http://target-site.com
Python/Node.js Conflicts: Use virtualenv (Python) or nvm (Node.js) to manage versions.

Security: Never hardcode API keys—use environment variables or a secrets manager like AWS Secrets Manager.